@NODE "Device" "Part 55 - The INFO Command - The DEVICE Option"

@{B}@{U}The DEVICE Option@{UU} Version 1.3 onwards@{UB}

If you add the name of a device (with or without the "DEVICE" keyword)
on the command line, as in one of these:-

  INFO DEVICE df1:
  INFO df1:

then you are given the information for that drive only. For example:-

  Mounted Disks:
  DF1:      837K    1648     110  94%   0  Read/Write Games

  Volumes available:
  Games [Mounted]

If no disk is present then the output would be:-

  Mounted disks:
  Unit      Size    Used    Free Full Errs   Status   Name
  DF1:      No disk present

  Volumes available:
  DF1 [Mounted]

@{B}Version 1.3 Note:@{UB} this option does not give a "Volumes Available" heading.

